"Packaged on date read 6/3/14. Poured into my Prima Pils cylindrical glass. Dark copper to light amber. Crystal clear with very nice carbonation and rocky foamy head that lingers. Some sweet toasted malts. Some spicy hops and maybe some faint citrus. Malty upfront with toast and some light caramel. Breadiness from the malts lingers with just a touch of bitterness to lend the proper balance. Feels slightly chewy giving it a medium to full body. Malt is dominant, and proves to be a well made beer. Appreciated this beer much more the second time around. Would go great with some German fare like brats & sauerkraut."
