"another well made but somewhat unexciting beer from the beer camp box. ive liked victory a lot lately, and this is indeed a nice alt, with a little bit of a tannic malt sting before the clean finish, i think its intentionally and a nice twist to cut the sweeter red malt and to balance the fruity middle of this. its a red beer with a lot of character, rusty in color, clear as they come, and nice and frothy. there is a pretty decent hop profile on it too, english or german bittering varietals primarily, and i find this to be a rather authentic take on the style overall. a quicker finish for a red beer too, which i like. medium bodied and very robustly carbonated, it drinks a little lighter than it is. not the most remarkable brew in the box, but i must say i enjoyed this interpretation of altbier very well. maybe next year they will do more exciting stuff with styles, but this year i am thankful just for the opportunity to drink some cool new stuff, even if it is a little weak on the adventurous scale."
