"Poured into an Euler stange. Pours a nice red coppery amber with a one finger khaki head with good retention and lacing. Unusual aroma of sweet malt and floral hops, not quite what I expected or like anything else I've had; intriguing. Flavor is drier biscuit malt with only hints of caramel, light rye and fruit sourness, with grassy, mildly citrus hops that linger into a spicy, mildly herbal hop finish with dark bread and rye. Light to medium bodied with active carbonation. Not a traditional altbier, although the basic darker biscuit malt, light fruitiness, hops and basic dryness are present. There is a rye-like mild tartness and flavor although there is apparently no rye in this brew. As a rye fan, this is no distraction. An idiosyncratic, but nice take on a altbier. The somewhat more aggressive hops, expected from Victory, work well here. I liked this a lot and as my first beer from the pack, a very positive start."
